       sulogin

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       sulogin  is  automatically invoked by init when the system
       is first started.  It prompts the user to  type  the  root
       password  to  enter  system  maintenance mode (single-user
       mode) or to type EOF  (typically  D)  for  normal  startup
       (multi-user   mode).   sulogin  should  never  be  invoked
       directly by the user.

